# Implementation Plan - Mobile-first Polished Mood Dashboard (Issue 06)

We will reorganize the React frontend into a premium, single-page application with a tab-based view controller, matching the design details in [issues/06-mobile-first-polished-mood-dashboard.md](file:///c:/Users/Surya/Documents/mental-wellness-tracker/issues/06-mobile-first-polished-mood-dashboard.md) and [image.png](file:///c:/Users/Surya/Documents/mental-wellness-tracker/image.png). We will also fix the syntax errors and missing definitions in [App.jsx](file:///c:/Users/Surya/Documents/mental-wellness-tracker/frontend/src/App.jsx).

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Reorganizing into Tabs**:
> Currently, the app renders all components on a single long scrolling page. We propose split-screen views controlled by a bottom navigation bar:
> 1. **`landing` (Landing Screen)**: Renders a friendly welcome screen with cartoon-expression floating shapes and a bold CTA: *"Not Sure About Your Mood? Let Us Help! →"*.
> 2. **`home` (Home Dashboard)**: Date header, greeting, quick-mood selection buttons, interactive metrics grid (Sleep, Stress, Quiz), and the Journal entry form.
> 3. **`calendar` (Mood Calendar)**: Month day grid showing color-coded emoji logs, dominant Monthly Mood Summary card, and supplementary tracking metrics (Steps, Therapy, Focus score).
> 4. **`trends` (Insights & Analytics)**: Preserves the Weekly Mood Pulse SVG chart and recent journal entries list.
> 5. **`coping` (Companion Guide)**: Displays the daily Coping Companion guide and crisis helpline support resources.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Interactive Quiz Widget**:
> We will add an interactive wellness quiz card in the metrics grid. Answering Yes/No to 4 simple questions gives the user personalized wellness advice based on their answers.

